              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Tue, 17 Mar. 2020&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN RESOURCES &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;HUMAN RESOURCES OFFICER (x2); 1 BASED AT THE MAIN CAMPUS &amp; THE OTHER ONE AT ORI (MAUN) - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;IRC 855&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A minimum of bachelor Degree in Social Sciences or related area.  In addition candidates should have strong interpersonal and communication skills, organizational skills, negotiating skills; should be assertive and pro-active. Knowledge of computerized Human Resources record system is essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;:  Candidates should have at least six months on-the-job training in University’s employment policies, practices and procedures. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: &lt;span&gt;The successful candidate shall be expected to: (1) advise departments and faculties on the application of the University’s General Conditions of Service; (ii) implement the University’s procedures for the recruitment of staff and provides professional and administrative support to appointment and selection committees; (iii) ensure that new employees complete recruitment formalities and contracts and assist with the induction of new employees; (iv) work closely with departments and faculties on the identification of manpower requirements and training and development needs; (v) assist with the development of manpower budgets and estimates and the preparation of manpower forecasts and statistics; (vi) supervise the accurate maintenance of computerized HR record systems and prepares statistical reports and analysis as required; (vii) establish and ensure implementation of filing and record systems; (viii)  attend to and resolve employee complaints and grievances; (ix) prepare draft appointment, promotion, transfer, dismissal, etc. letters as directed in accordance with Human Resource policies; (x) process and review applications in terms of the University’s various welfare, allowance and benefits schemes and authorize applications within delegated authorities; coordinate performance management reviews and assists user departments with the implementation of performance management systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The University of Botswana offers a competitive salary and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.  For more information on the University, please visit our website: &lt;a href="http://www.ub.bw/"&gt;www.ub.bw&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to Apply&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Letters of applications are to address stated qualifications and provide any other information to assist the University to determine the applicants’ suitability for the position.  You should quote the vacancy number of the post applied for; provide current CVs (including telephone numbers and email), certified true copies of educational certificates, transcripts and names and addresses of three referees. Applicants should inform their referees to &lt;span&gt;(i) &lt;strong&gt;Quote the Vacancy Number(s) and Position applied for&lt;/strong&gt; and (ii) &lt;strong&gt;submit their references directly to the address below&lt;/strong&gt; before the stipulated closing date. Send your applications to: &lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;he Human Resources Manager, Appointments and Administration (Support), University of Botswana, Private Bag 0022, GABORONE, Telephone: 267 355 2040/5731.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted at &lt;strong&gt;Block 108 Office No 205 (108/205).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

